"""
A simple behavioural task to assess a Simon effect.

See also:
http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Simon_effect

"""

Tests count: 1
Screens: [<Screen:Practice>, <Screen:Real>]

Variables:
    positions = [left, right]
    colors = [green, red]
    responses = [left, right]



Test: Simon
--------------------------------------------------------------------------

Conditions:

| position | color | congruency  | response |
|----------+-------+-------------+----------|
| left     | green | congruent   | left     |
| left     | red   | incongruent | right    |
| right    | green | incongruent | left     |
| right    | red   | congruent   | right    |


Detailed with stimuli for each trial:

| position | color | congruency  | response |
|----------+-------+-------------+----------|
| left     | green | congruent   | left     |

  Variables:
    positions = [left, right]
    colors = [green, red]
    responses = [left, right]
    position = left
    color = green
    congruency = congruent
    response = left

  Phases:
    fix:
            at 0 cross() for 0
    exec:
            at 0 rectangle(posx left, color green, fillColor green) for 0
    error:
            at 0 sound(freq 1000) for 300
    correct:
            at 0 sound(freq 500) for 300


| position | color | congruency  | response |
|----------+-------+-------------+----------|
| left     | red   | incongruent | right    |

  Variables:
    positions = [left, right]
    colors = [green, red]
    responses = [left, right]
    position = left
    color = red
    congruency = incongruent
    response = right

  Phases:
    fix:
            at 0 cross() for 0
    exec:
            at 0 rectangle(posx left, color red, fillColor red) for 0
    error:
            at 0 sound(freq 1000) for 300
    correct:
            at 0 sound(freq 500) for 300


| position | color | congruency  | response |
|----------+-------+-------------+----------|
| right    | green | incongruent | left     |

  Variables:
    positions = [left, right]
    colors = [green, red]
    responses = [left, right]
    position = right
    color = green
    congruency = incongruent
    response = left

  Phases:
    fix:
            at 0 cross() for 0
    exec:
            at 0 rectangle(posx right, color green, fillColor green) for 0
    error:
            at 0 sound(freq 1000) for 300
    correct:
            at 0 sound(freq 500) for 300


| position | color | congruency  | response |
|----------+-------+-------------+----------|
| right    | red   | congruent   | right    |

  Variables:
    positions = [left, right]
    colors = [green, red]
    responses = [left, right]
    position = right
    color = red
    congruency = congruent
    response = right

  Phases:
    fix:
            at 0 cross() for 0
    exec:
            at 0 rectangle(posx right, color red, fillColor red) for 0
    error:
            at 0 sound(freq 1000) for 300
    correct:
            at 0 sound(freq 500) for 300


